        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2373243463" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer685619939695933791"><strong>Interesting, but politically slanted at times</strong><br/><br/>This is a highly technical, dense history of the NSA through the end of 2001. However, Bamford spends too much time getting in digs against people and policies he disagrees with. For instance, the postscript after 9/11 talks about how NSA wastes too much money and effort in eavesdropping on China. However, China&apos;s been a hostile power engaging in trade espionage against the US for decades.</span>
